tle":"Author/Tchadji Mayoudom Vanessa","target":"Author/Tchadji Mayoudom Vanessa","line":96},{"title":"Author/Tchadji Mayoudom Vanessa","target":"Author/Tchadji Mayoudom Vanessa","line":97},{"title":"Author/Tchadji Mayoudom Vanessa","target":"Author/Tchadji Mayoudom Vanessa","line":98},{"title":"Author/Dobgima John Fomnboh","target":"Author/Dobgima John Fomnboh","line":99},{"title":"Author/Dobgima John Fomnboh","target":"Author/Dobgima John Fomnboh","line":100},{"title":"Author/Dobgima John Fomnboh","target":"Author/Dobgima John Fomnboh","line":101},{"title":"Author/C. N. Fokunang","target":"Author/C. N. Fokunang","line":102},{"title":"Author/Charles Fokunang","target":"Author/Charles Fokunang","line":103},{"title":"Author/Charles Fokunang","target":"Author/Charles Fokunang","line":104},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/fokunang_medicinal_2022/fokunang_medicinal_2022.pdf","line":106}],"metadata":{"id":"fokunang_medicinal_2022","type":"article-journal","title":"Medicinal Mushroom of Potential Pharmaceutical Toxic Importance: Contribution in Phytotherapy","issued":{"date-parts":[[2022]]},"DOI":"10.5772/intechopen.103845","container-title":"null","abstract":"Orthodox medical practice depends greatly on the use of high throughput (HTP) pure pharmaceutical new chemical entities, with a purity that can easily be evaluated and whose efficacy and toxicity can show a dose-dependent, clear structure-activity relationships (SAR). On the contrary, natural products contain mixtures of natural bioactive metabolites that have not undergone any chemical analyses and whose mechanism of action is not known. Medicinal mushrooms have been used throughout the history of mankind for the treatment of various diseases including cancer. Nowadays they have been intensively studied and generated research interest in an attempt to reveal the chemical nature and mechanisms of action of their bioactive molecules. Targeted treatment of diseases, non-harmful for healthy tissues, has become a major objective in recent times and metabolites of fungal origin provide a vast reservoir of potential new chemical entities. There are many examples of mushrooms common for use globally that demonstrate the complex nature of their pharmaceutical potential This review paper attempts to show that some aspects of fungotherapy of the disease have been well studied. We also give an insight into the role of mushroom metabolites for treatment of diseases types that are especially susceptible to the fungal treatments.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Fokunang","given":"Estella Tembe","literal":""},{"family":"Fokunang","given":"Estella Tembe","literal":""},{"family":"Fokunang","given":"Estella Tembe","literal":""},{"family":"Annih","given":"Mbong Grace","literal":""},{"family":"Annih","given":"Mbong Grace","literal":""},{"family":"Annih","given":"Mbong Grace","literal":""},{"family":"Abongwa","given":"Lem Edith","literal":""},{"family":"Abongwa","given":"Lem Edith","literal":""},{"family":"Abongwa","given":"Lem Edith","literal":""},{"family":"Bih","given":"Manju Evelyn","literal":""},{"family":"Bih","given":"Manju Evelyn","literal":""},{"family":"Bih","given":"Manju Evelyn","literal":""},{"family":"Vanessa","given":"Tchadji Mayoudom","literal":""},{"family":"Vanessa","given":"Tchadji Mayoudom","literal":""},{"family":"Vanessa","given":"Tchadji Mayoudom","literal":""},{"family":"Fomnboh","given":"Dobgima John","literal":""},{"family":"Fomnboh","given":"Dobgima John","literal":""},{"family":"Fomnboh","given":"Dobgima John","literal":""},{"family":"Fokunang","given":"C. N.","literal":""},{"family":"Fokunang","given":"Charles","literal":""},{"family":"Fokunang","given":"Charles","literal":""}],"citation-key":"fokunang_medicinal_2022","year":"2022","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Medicinal Mushroom of Potential Pharmaceutical Toxic Importance: Contribution in Phytotherapy"],"author-links":["[[Author/Estella Tembe Fokunang]]","[[Author/